The paper deals with voltage control in power distribution systems, which is a problem in control theory and systems engineering. The use of game theory and distributed algorithms suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY) and game theory (cs.GT). The paper also mentions optimization algorithms, which could fall under machine learning (cs.MA). The use of communication networks suggests a possible category of networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). Finally, the numerical tests and convergence results suggest a possible category of machine learning and statistics (cs.LG).
